    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "polling_cq in the first change is declared static __thread (making it thread local).\n\nFWIW I'm torn between taking thread locals, and plumbing through some kind of global context object that gets created (on the stack) at our public entry points and passed through everywhere - such an object could help clarify the boundaries of some of these operations a little more strongly than thread locals could, but would of course mean a bunch of typing for someone.\n"
